            <h3>Linux support</h3>
            <p>Support for certain Linux virtual machine images in the Azure Marketplace is available from the publisher. In some cases, it is provided by the publisher for free. In other cases, we charge by the minute for the right to receive support. The total charge for running a Linux VM is the support rate (if applicable) plus the Linux compute rate. Microsoft does not provide support for Linux images in the Azure Marketplace.</p>
<p>Free trial, MSDN, BizSpark and Microsoft Partner Network member benefits (monetary credits) do not apply to publisher provided Linux support, which is billed separately. However, if you are on a 6 or 12-Month Purchase Plan or the 12-Month Commitment Offer, your commitment balance can be used for Linux support charges until 30th June 2016. Afterwards, license charges for the support provided by Linux publishers will be billed separately and will not be discounted (consistent with all third-party products). Linux support charges are billed separately for Enterprise Agreement customers and are not deducted from prepaid monetary commitment (consistent with all third-party products).</p>

            <h3>SUSE Linux Enterprise Server (SLES) images</h3>
            <p>Azure Virtual Machines can be deployed from SLES Basic and SLES Premium images available in the Azure Marketplace. Customers who deploy SLES Basic images are entitled to receive patching from SUSE for those VMs at no additional charge over the compute rates. Customers who deploy SLES Premium images are entitled to receive both patching and telephone and email support from SUSE for those VMs at the support rates listed below. These prices apply to both Basic and Standard VM instance sizes.</p>

